**No Solicitation of Transactions (page 74)**

The merger agreement contains detailed provisions that prohibit WaferGen and its subsidiaries, directors, officers, employees and representatives from, directly or indirectly, soliciting, initiating or knowingly encouraging, knowingly facilitating or cooperating in any way with any third party in connection with an alternative acquisition proposal from a third party or conducting or engaging in discussions or negotiations with, or disclosing any non-public information relating to WaferGen or its subsidiaries to, a third party that is seeking to make an alternative acquisition proposal. The merger agreement does, however, permit WaferGen to waive any standstill or similar provisions in an agreement between WaferGen and a third party if the WaferGen board of directors determines in good faith that failure to take action in order to permit an alternative acquisition proposal from any such third party would cause the board of directors to breach its fiduciary duties under applicable law. Furthermore, the merger agreement does not prohibit WaferGen’s board of directors from considering and recommending to WaferGen stockholders an alternative acquisition proposal from a third party if specified conditions are met, including the payment of a termination fee as required under the merger agreement.

